sentences: Afro-dite came together to sing the song "Never Let It Go" for the Eurovision Song Contest 2002.
In 2007 they released a new album.[1]
In 2012, they made another attempt for Eurovision with the song, "The Boy Can Dance", but were eliminated in the first semi-final of Melodifestivalen.
Gladys, born in Ecuador, came to Sweden when she was only 7 years old.
